<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0">
    <teiHeader><fileDesc><titleStmt><title>General Marshall to the Chief
                        of Staff (
                        Eisenhower
                    )</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1946v10</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d493</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">493</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1946-06-06T00:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1946-06-06T23:59:59-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-06-06T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-06-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="493" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d493">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Marshall Mission Files, Lot 54–D270:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">General <persName type="from">Marshall</persName> to the Chief
                        of Staff</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Eisenhower</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-06-06">6 June
                            1946</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>823. It was suggested by me to Doctor T. V. Soong that the Chinese Government
                    might wish to notify the Chinese Supply Commission in Washington of its approval
                    for purchase of Chinese manned Liberty <pb facs="0805" n="795" xml:id="pg_795"/>
                    ships reference 89251.<note n="59" xml:id="d493fn59">Telegram of May 24, not
                        printed.</note> Doctor Soong informs me that Minister Yu Ta-wei<note n="60" xml:id="d493fn60">Chinese Minister of Communications.</note> will give
                    immediate approval to formal application for purchase.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
